Heatmap Script - Automatically Infer yMax Values from Matrix

2-26-26 Update

In[1]:
#!/usr/bin/env bash

module load deeptools

set -euo pipefail
export MPLBACKEND=Agg

# =========================
# INPUT BASE DIRECTORY
# =========================
BASEDIR="/data/gallegosda/GEO/Figures/HeatmapScript_2-25-26"

# =========================
# INPUT FILES
# =========================
REGIONS_BED="${BASEDIR}/genes_bound_in_ESCs_master_homer_file_3163_now_3132_GREAT.bed"
BIGWIG_TSV="${BASEDIR}/tracks_mm10_ncPRC16_DG.tsv"   # format: label <TAB> /path/to/bw [<TAB> colormap]
BLACKLIST="${BASEDIR}/89_of_top200_3163_ESC_and_145_of_top200_1804_MEF_blacklist_234.bed"

# =========================
# PARAMETERS
# =========================
UPSTREAM=2000
DOWNSTREAM=2000
BIN_SIZE=25
THREADS=4

# =========================
# OUTPUTS
# =========================
OUTDIR="${BASEDIR}/deeptools_TSS"
mkdir -p "${OUTDIR}"

BW_LIST="${OUTDIR}/bigwigs.list.txt"
LABELS_LIST="${OUTDIR}/labels.list.txt"
CMAP_LIST="${OUTDIR}/cmaps.list.txt"

# =========================
# PARSE TSV FILE
# =========================
# Clear old files if they exist
rm -f "${BW_LIST}" "${LABELS_LIST}" "${CMAP_LIST}"

awk '
NR==1 {next}          # skip header
NF==0 {next}          # skip blank lines
{
  gsub("\r","")
  bw=""; bw_i=0
  
  # Find bigwig file (ends in .bw or .bigwig)
  for (i=1; i<=NF; i++) {
    if (tolower($i) ~ /\.(bw|bigwig)$/) { 
      bw=$i
      bw_i=i
      break
    }
  }
  
  if (bw=="") { 
    print "ERROR: No bigwig file found in line: " $0 > "/dev/stderr"
    next 
  }

  # Extract colormap (last field, or default)
  cmap="RdYlBu"
  if (NF > bw_i && !($NF ~ /\.bw$/)) {
    cmap=$NF
  }

  # Label is first field
  label=$1

  print bw    >> bw_out
  print label >> lab_out
  print cmap  >> cmap_out
}
' bw_out="${BW_LIST}" lab_out="${LABELS_LIST}" cmap_out="${CMAP_LIST}" "${BIGWIG_TSV}"

echo "Parsed files:"
echo "  BigWigs: $(wc -l < "${BW_LIST}")"
echo "  Labels : $(wc -l < "${LABELS_LIST}")"
echo "  CMAPs  : $(wc -l < "${CMAP_LIST}")"
echo "  Regions: $(wc -l < "${REGIONS_BED}")"

# =========================
# BUILD ARGUMENT LISTS
# =========================
BIGWIGS=""
while IFS= read -r bw; do
  [[ -z "$bw" ]] && continue
  BIGWIGS="${BIGWIGS} ${bw}"
done < "${BW_LIST}"

LABELS=""
while IFS= read -r lab; do
  [[ -z "$lab" ]] && continue
  LABELS="${LABELS} ${lab}"
done < "${LABELS_LIST}"

CMAPS=""
while IFS= read -r cm; do
  [[ -z "$cm" ]] && continue
  CMAPS="${CMAPS} ${cm}"
done < "${CMAP_LIST}"

# =========================
# STEP 1: Sort regions using first track
# =========================
BW1=$(sed -n '1p' "${BW_LIST}")
LABEL1=$(sed -n '1p' "${LABELS_LIST}")

MATRIX_1="${OUTDIR}/matrix_TSS_track1_for_sort.gz"
SORTED_REGIONS="${OUTDIR}/regions_sorted_by_track1_fixed.bed"

echo "Step 1: Computing matrix for track 1 (for sorting)..."
computeMatrix reference-point \
  --referencePoint center \
  -R "${REGIONS_BED}" \
  -S "${BW1}" \
  -b "${UPSTREAM}" -a "${DOWNSTREAM}" \
  --binSize "${BIN_SIZE}" \
  --missingDataAsZero \
  --numberOfProcessors "${THREADS}" \
  --blackListFileName ${BLACKLIST} \
  -o "${MATRIX_1}" \
  --outFileNameMatrix "${OUTDIR}/IndividualValues_777.tab"

echo "Generating sort order from track 1..."
plotHeatmap \
  -m "${MATRIX_1}" \
  -out "${OUTDIR}/heatmap_track1_for_sort_000.pdf" \
  --whatToShow "plot, heatmap and colorbar" \
  --plotType lines \
  --refPointLabel "TSS" \
  --samplesLabel "${LABEL1}" \
  --averageTypeSummaryPlot mean \
  --sortRegions descend \
  --sortUsing mean \
  --colorMap Reds \
  --outFileSortedRegions "${SORTED_REGIONS}"

echo " DONE! see heatmap_track1_for_sort.pdf"

# =========================
# STEP 2: Compute matrix for ALL tracks
# =========================
MATRIX_ALL="${OUTDIR}/matrix_TSS_ALL.gz"

echo "Step 2: Computing matrix for all tracks..."
computeMatrix reference-point \
  --referencePoint center \
  -R "${SORTED_REGIONS}" \
  -S ${BIGWIGS} \
  -b "${UPSTREAM}" -a "${DOWNSTREAM}" \
  --binSize "${BIN_SIZE}" \
  --missingDataAsZero \
  --numberOfProcessors "${THREADS}" \
  --blackListFileName ${BLACKLIST} \
  -o "${MATRIX_ALL}" \
  --outFileNameMatrix "${OUTDIR}/IndividualValues_ALLPLOTS.tab"

# =========================
# STEP 3: Get yMax values
# =========================

echo "Step 3: Computing yMax values (98th percentile) from Matrix for all tracks..."

# Clean up .tab
N_REGIONS=$(wc -l < "$REGIONS_BED")
sed "s/genes:${N_REGIONS}\t/genes:${N_REGIONS}\n/" "${OUTDIR}/IndividualValues_ALLPLOTS.tab" > "${OUTDIR}/IndividualValues_ALLPLOTS_fixed.tab"

# Get yMax values using 96 percentile
TAB="${OUTDIR}/IndividualValues_ALLPLOTS_fixed.tab"
N_SAMPLES=9
BINS=160
PERCENTILE=98

YMAX_ARGS=""

for i in $(seq 0 $((N_SAMPLES - 1))); do
    COL_START=$((1 + i * BINS))
    COL_END=$((COL_START + BINS - 1))

    YMAX=$(awk -v start="$COL_START" -v end="$COL_END" 'NR > 3 {
            for (col = start; col <= end; col++)
                if ($col != "nan") print $col
        }' "$TAB" \
        | sort -n \
        | awk -v pct="$PERCENTILE" '
            { vals[NR] = $1 }
            END { print vals[int(NR * pct / 100)] }
        ')

    echo "Sample $((i+1)) yMax: $YMAX"
    YMAX_ARGS="$YMAX_ARGS $YMAX"
done

# =========================
# STEP 4: Generate final heatmap
# =========================
LABELS_STR=$(echo "${LABELS[@]}" | tr ' ' '_')
HEATMAP_FILE="heatmap_multipanel_${LABELS_STR}"

OUTPDF_MULTI="${OUTDIR}/${HEATMAP_FILE}.pdf"

echo "Step 4: Generating final heatmap..."
plotHeatmap \
  -m "${MATRIX_ALL}" \
  -out "${OUTPDF_MULTI}" \
  --whatToShow "plot, heatmap and colorbar" \
  --plotType lines \
  --samplesLabel ${LABELS} \
  --colorMap ${CMAPS} \
  --boxAroundHeatmaps no \
  --yMin 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 \
  --yMax $YMAX_ARGS \
  --zMin 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 \
  --zMax $YMAX_ARGS  

convert "${OUTDIR}/${HEATMAP_FILE}.pdf" "${OUTDIR}/${HEATMAP_FILE}.png"
cp "${OUTDIR}/${HEATMAP_FILE}.png" "${BASEDIR}/${HEATMAP_FILE}.png"

echo " DONE! Output: ${OUTPDF_MULTI}"
